alism in the post-crisis era, History in Financial Times traces the diverse modes of history production at work in the spheres of financial journalism, policymaking, and popular culture. Paying particular attention to narrative and to notions of crisis, recurrence, and revelation, Amin Samman gives us a novel take on the relation between historical thinking and critique.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEconomicsxPhilosophy. 0aFinancexHistory. 0aFinancial crisesxHistory. 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009. 0aHistoryxPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aFinancialization.  acapitalism.  acrisis.  ahistorical imagination.  ahistory.  anarrative.  arecurrence.  arevelation.  astrange loops.  atime.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360946440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609464423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609464.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-PLWb2020